{
  "texts": [
    "While AI can automate the discovery of connections and the generation of hypotheses, the task of testing those hypotheses may remain human and SLP led (Mollick, 2024).",
    "To fully leverage AI's potential, it will be essential to utilize the extensive datasets accumulated by disciplinary journals and theses in university archives.",
    "These datasets can be used to train models, generate insights from related but distant domains, and create or test novel hypotheses when knowledge gaps are identified (Agrawal et al., 2023).",
    "Given its extensive archives, ASHA could play a pivotal role by monetizing its datasets, which could support both clinical training and research.",
    "Ensuring the use of accurate, cleaned, and reviewed datasets is critical to minimizing hallucinations in AI-generated outputs (Ji et al., 2023)."
  ]
}